In English it would sound strange to say "I left NO TIP" but it works for the puzzle. I would say "I didn't leave a tip."

We also have this idiom: "leaves nothing (or a lot) to be desired," although I would say it's used more in print than spoken. As in, "the dinner was excellent; it left nothing to be desired."

